3. Role Definitions
3.1 Super Admin
Description

The Super Admin manages the Clinora platform and all tenant organizations.

This role is intended only for the Clinora operations team.

Responsibilities
Onboard clinics
Manage subscriptions
Monitor platform health
View tenant usage
Configure platform settings
Manage feature flags
Support tenant onboarding

Cannot:

Edit clinical records
Write prescriptions
Modify consultations
3.2 Clinic Administrator
Description

Owns and manages one clinic.

Responsible for business operations.

Responsibilities
Configure clinic
Manage doctors
Manage reception staff
Manage lab staff
Configure schedules
Configure consultation fees
View analytics
View revenue
Configure payment settings
Configure branding

Cannot:

Access another clinic
Modify platform settings
3.3 Reception / Clinic Staff
Description

Handles patient operations.

Responsibilities
Register patients
Search patients
Book appointments
Reschedule appointments
Cancel appointments
Register walk-ins
Check-in patients
Collect payments
Print invoices
Manage waiting queue

Cannot

Write prescriptions
Upload lab reports
View financial analytics
Configure clinic settings
3.4 Doctor
Description

Primary healthcare provider.

Responsibilities
View appointments
Search assigned patients
Access patient timeline
Record consultations
Add diagnoses
Write prescriptions
Request laboratory tests
Review reports
Schedule follow-ups

Cannot

Modify billing
Manage staff
Configure clinic settings
3.5 Laboratory Staff
Description

Responsible for diagnostics.

Responsibilities
View lab requests
Collect samples
Update sample status
Upload reports
Notify doctor
Notify patient

Cannot

Modify prescriptions
View clinic revenue
Manage appointments
3.6 Patient
Description

End user receiving healthcare.

Responsibilities
Register
Login
Book appointments
Cancel appointments
Pay invoices
Download reports
Download prescriptions
View history
Update profile

Cannot

View other patients
Access doctor dashboard
Access clinic administration
4. Permission Levels

Every module follows one of these permissions.

Permission	Description
View	Read information
Create	Add new records
Update	Modify existing records
Delete	Remove records
Approve	Administrative approval
Export	Download reports
Configure	Change settings
