11. Security Principles

Clinora follows the principle of Least Privilege.

Users receive only the minimum permissions necessary to perform their responsibilities.

Role permissions are managed centrally and enforced consistently across the frontend, backend, APIs, and database.

12. Future Enhancements

The role management system is designed to support:

Custom Roles
Custom Permissions
Department-Based Access
Attribute-Based Access Control (ABAC)
Multi-Clinic Users
Temporary Access
Approval Workflows
External Identity Providers (Google, Microsoft Entra ID, Okta)
Document Summary

This document defines the security and access model for Clinora. It serves as the foundation for UI visibility, backend authorization, API security, and database isolation.
